race.comment: JACKA STANDS ALONE (4) resumes for Pat Webster off an Open 3 win at Rockhampton. He's proven first-up and owns a 7.3L Gatton trial win. This is a suitable kick-off point and a bold run is on the cards. TAKEMINE (10) was outgraded in town and then was back on track beaten  2.25L over 1100m at Armidale. Looker rides today, and she tumbles in weight. That brings her right into it. I AM A WINNER (5) was back in the winners' circle on the same day. He's switched from a Sydney barn and has been racing at provincial level. Keeps the 2kg claim and he can make the finish. MR ENCORE (7) went close twice at Gatton and the speedy galloper can't be ruled out.
